Pancreatology
    Risk factors for acute kidney injury after pancreatoduodenectomy, and association with postoperative complications and death.
Postoperative AKI was associated with major postoperative complications and an increased risk of postoperative mortality. Monitoring changes in serum creatinine levels and urine volume output could be important in the immediate perioperative period to improve outcomes after pancreatoduodenectomy.
